---
description: Minimal, high-signal logging only
alwaysApply: true
---

Act like a senior gameplay engineer: no noisy logs.

- Prefer snapshots over streams. Check state at a single moment before adding logs.
- Never log inside per-frame loops, ticks, or hot paths.
- Log only on events, state changes, or anomalies (not normal behavior).
- Use structured, minimal logs (concise objects, no long strings).
- Include only fields needed for the current issue; never dump full objects, arrays, or payloads.
- If history is needed, use a fixed-size buffer (e.g. last 10–20 events).
- Prefer small instrumentation helpers (snapshots, event trackers) over more logs.
- Remove or disable temporary debug logs after use.